Implemented lazy loading for ArcGIS map components through the newly introduced arcgis-assets.ts module.

Changes Made

* Created a centralized asset loader (arcgis-assets.ts) to manage ArcGIS component imports.
* Converted map widgets/components to dynamic imports instead of loading them during initial application startup.
* Added component-specific loader methods for widgets such as Zoom, Home, Scale Bar, Basemap Gallery, and other ArcGIS UI components.
* Ensured each component is loaded only once and reused across the application.
* Reduced unnecessary upfront JavaScript loading and initialization overhead.

Benefits

* Improved initial map load performance.
* Reduced application startup time by loading components on demand.
* Prevented loading unused ArcGIS widgets.
* Improved scalability for future ArcGIS components and widgets.
* Centralized asset management, making maintenance and troubleshooting easier.

Technical Approach

* Introduced dynamic import() based loading.
* Implemented singleton-style loader promises to avoid duplicate component registration and downloads.
* Separated ArcGIS asset initialization from map rendering logic.
* Maintained backward compatibility with existing UPMap APIs and consumer applications.